Hi Everyone, 

I am looking to build out my set. Currently, I have 54. Given the volume, in an effort to minimize back and forth, I am looking to pay the price from the PSA guide (path at bottom). If you have cards that fit the criteria, assuming I don't already have that card, I am willing buy it/them off of you at the price listed below. 

[url]https://www.psacard.com/priceguide/baseball-card-values/1909-11-t206-white-border/1055[/url]

Thanks! 
Taylor

Best of luck! Just a heads up, the prices in the link seem to be pretty out of date, at least for the bigger names. I looked up a few and just as an example, it's saying a cy young portrait psa 2 would be 1300. If anyone is selling one for under 2300 (a full 1k over "book"), I'd love to see it.
Agreed on the big names. For commons though, it's a good way for me to acquire a bunch at once or for someone with a lot of them to unload them for a quick payday.

even the commons pricing is badly lagging the market.

for example the PSA guide has Dave Brain in psa5 at "150+"

The last three sales are $492, $660, and $480
PSA 5s usually go between 250-350 depending on player with common backs...off backs are only up from there. I would not pay too much attention to these prices
